                        Prioritising knowledge and education 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Education and Research, 05.10.2010]</p>
                <p>In 2011, allocations to education and knowledge increase with the total of NOK 4.6 billion. -We are pleased that the government, within a tight budget, has chosen to prioritise the most important investment that we can make in our future – the education sector, say the ministers Kristin Halvorsen and Tora Aasland.</p>
                
                
